  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> O.K., this deck is more for fun than anything else but it&#8217;s listed as advanced because it has a few rares, not because it takes a genius or anything to play it.  I don&#8217;t think I would ever use it in a tournament because dwarves and elves just need too much stuff to make them really wail, a la event boosters, rare weapons, Aragron for that little whore Arwen, etc., etc.  Mainly I was just tired of using my Rangers or Gandalf&#8230;every...single...time&#8230;must ...find...something&#8230;different.  Anyhoo, just a deck I use when my buddies and I play.  So far the one thing elves and dwarves really lack are ways to heal themselves.  I know dwarves have the whole Still Draws Breath thing but it&#8217;s dependent on winning.  Hobbits and Men have the-one-card-fix-it-stuff like Athelas and Stout and Sturdy.  Well, work with what you have I say and hope Mines of Moria rocks.<br />
<br />
Fellowship revolves around, you guessed it, elves and dwarves.  No Gondor, no Rangers allowed.  Also makes use of some Shire stuff to make those sorry little bastards pull their own weight.  No free rides you little freaks!  Start with Gimli and Legolas.  Draw Merry, Friend to Sam, later or, if by some chance I get to go first, pull him with Maggot&#8217;s Fields, yeah me.  Use the four to move (slowly) through the Path, occasionally able to rock the big boys with Merry exerting to add his strength to Gimli.  Gimli+Gimli exerting to boost his strength+his axe+Lord of Moria+Merry=kill anything.  Shoulder to Shoulder, Farmer Maggot to heal.  Put Tale of Gil-Galad on Elrond and use him to make sure Gimli is healthy.  Grimir can help out Legolas.  Let me know what else would work (only Shire, Elves, or Dwarves).<br />
<br />
Shadow is Moria because I&#8217;m able to clear my hand well with them.  Plus, I finally have three Cave Trolls.  When I have won with this deck it&#8217;s been because of the Shadow side, not because I beat anybody to Site 9.  Anyhoo, like I said, a fun deck with three characters I hardly ever use.<br />
